If I can be super-picky (sorry!) I'd suggest the conditionals should be:
if (producer == null)
{
   // ...
}
At the moment all the if ... statements look more like function calls with the ( coming immediately after if without any space in-between, and instead a space between the ( and the variable used for comparison -- just looks messy...

